HEADWORD: Gruiformes
<hw>Gruiformes</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An order of inland marsh-dwelling
birds with long legs and necks and bills that wade in water in search of
food, including cranes, rails, and bustards.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Gruiformes</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

